# Mastra MCP — docs lookup for iPix

**Live config:** `~/.cursor/mcp.json` → server id **`mastra`** (Cursor exposes as **`user-mastra`**).  
**Repo template:** `.cursor/mcp.example.json` (install: `bash scripts/cursor-mcp-setup.sh`)  
**Skill hub:** `.claude/skills/mastra/SKILL.md` · MCP matrix: `.claude/skills/mastra/references/mcp-docs-lookup.md`  
**Official:** [Build with AI](https://mastra.ai/docs/getting-started/build-with-ai) · [Get started](https://mastra.ai/docs) · Doc index: [mastra.ai/llms.txt](https://mastra.ai/llms.txt)

## Skills vs MCP (Mastra recommendation)

| Layer | When to use |
|-------|-------------|
| **Mastra skills** (`npx skills add mastra-ai/skills`) | Default for agents — setup, best practices, CLI; **better accuracy** than MCP alone |
| **`user-mastra` MCP** | Need MCP **tools** (migration, embedded package search, export discovery) |
| **Embedded `node_modules/@mastra/*/dist/docs`** | Package-local API truth — grep before guessing signatures |
| **Remote `.md` / `llms.txt`** | MCP miss or path 404 |

Per [Build with AI](https://mastra.ai/docs/getting-started/build-with-ai): prefer **skills** for documentation; use MCP when you need its tools (e.g. **`mastraMigration`**).

## Setup (do not regress)

```json
"mastra": {
  "type": "stdio",
  "command": "npx",
  "args": ["-y", "@mastra/mcp-docs-server@1.2.6"]
}
```

| ✅ Do | ❌ Don't |
|-------|---------|
| Enable **mastra** in Cursor **Settings → MCP** after config change | Assume MCP hot-reloads — **quit + reopen Cursor** |
| Use **Node.js ≥ 22.13.0** for `@mastra/mcp-docs-server@1.2.6` | Run on Node 20 — server stays **error**, tools missing |
| Pass **`projectPath`** = absolute path to **`app/`** (derive at runtime) | Hardcode a machine path or use repo root — wrong `node_modules` |
| Verify APIs from MCP + embedded docs before coding | Trust training-data Mastra APIs (they drift fast) |
| Use **`infisical run --env=dev --`** for dev commands needing `GEMINI_API_KEY` | Put API keys in MCP config |

### Resolve `projectPath` (required for embedded-doc tools)

```bash
# Absolute path to the operator app (owns node_modules/@mastra/*)
echo "$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/app"
```

Pass that value as `projectPath` on `searchMastraDocs`, `readMastraDocs`, `listMastraPackages`, `getMastraExports`.

### Node 22 fix

```bash
nvm install 22 && nvm use 22
node -v   # must be v22.13.0+
# optional: pin absolute npx in ~/.cursor/mcp.json if PATH fails in Cursor
which npx
```

### Enable after install

1. Save `~/.cursor/mcp.json` (or run `bash scripts/cursor-mcp-setup.sh`)
2. **Quit Cursor** completely
3. **Settings → MCP** → enable **mastra**
4. **New agent chat** (existing chats may not pick up tools)

## Tool pick (Cursor `user-mastra`)

| Need | Tool | Required args |
|------|------|---------------|
| Full doc page by path | **`mastraDocs`** | `paths: ["docs/agents/overview"]` |
| Browse embedded package docs | **`readMastraDocs`** | `package`, **`projectPath`** |
| Keyword search in installed docs | **`searchMastraDocs`** | `query`, **`projectPath`** |
| List installed `@mastra/*` | **`listMastraPackages`** | **`projectPath`** |
| Export / API surface | **`getMastraExports`** | `package`, **`projectPath`** |
| v0 → v1 migration | **`mastraMigration`** | per tool schema |

**Always:** `projectPath` = `$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)/app` (operator app owns `node_modules/@mastra/*`).

### `mastraDocs` path patterns

| Area | Example paths |
|------|---------------|
| Agents | `docs/agents/overview`, `reference/agents/generate`, `reference/agents/agent` |
| Memory | `docs/memory/working-memory`, `reference/memory/memory-class` |
| Workflows | `docs/workflows/suspend-and-resume`, `reference/workflows/workflow` |
| Tools | `reference/tools/create-tool` |
| Streaming | `reference/streaming/agents/stream` |
| CopilotKit | `guides/build-your-ui/copilotkit` |
| Build with AI / MCP | `docs/getting-started/build-with-ai` |
| Processors | `reference/processors/pii-detector`, `docs/agents/processors` |

Optional: `queryKeywords: ["CopilotKit", "stream"]` for related-path hints.

## Agent workflow

1. **Mastra change in `app/src/mastra/`** → load `.claude/skills/mastra/SKILL.md` + this rule.
2. **Need doc page** → `mastraDocs` with path from table above.
3. **Need installed API** → `searchMastraDocs` / `readMastraDocs` with runtime `projectPath` → `…/app`.
4. **Migration / breaking changes** → `mastraMigration` (MCP) or skill `references/migration-guide.md`.
5. **MCP empty / 404** → fallbacks below.

## Remote fallbacks (MCP miss)

1. Append **`.md`** to any Mastra docs URL — e.g. `https://mastra.ai/docs/agents/overview.md`
2. Per-page **`/llms.txt`** — e.g. `https://mastra.ai/docs/llms.txt`
3. Index: `curl -sL https://mastra.ai/llms.txt`
4. `.claude/skills/mastra/links.md` in repo
5. Remote MCP (last resort): `https://mastra.mcp.kapa.ai` — Google auth, rate-limited ([docs](https://mastra.ai/docs/getting-started/build-with-ai))

## iPix-specific (read before wiring)

| Topic | iPix pattern |
|-------|----------------|
| Code location | `app/src/mastra/` only — not root `src/` |
| Registry | `getMastra()` in handlers only — **never** top-level in routes |
| CLI export | Proxy `export const mastra` in `index.ts` for `mastra dev` |
| Model | Gemini via `models.ts` — `GEMINI_API_KEY` server-only |
| CopilotKit | **In-process** `MastraAgent.getLocalAgents()` in `/api/copilotkit` — not standalone `:4111/chat` |
| Agent IDs | `default`, `production-planner`, `creative-director`, … must match frontend `useAgent({ agentId })` |
| Storage | `DATABASE_URL` + `getMastraStorage()` — CI guard when unset |

Full gotchas: `CLAUDE.md` (Mastra section) + `app/AGENTS.md`.

## Mastra CLI (optional, complements MCP)

Global CLI talks to a **running** Mastra dev server (`:4111`):

```bash
npm install -g mastra@latest
cd app && infisical run --env=dev -- npm run dev   # Next :3002 + Mastra :4111
mastra api --url http://localhost:4111 agent run production-planner '{"messages":"..."}'
mastra api --url http://localhost:4111 trace list
```

Install Mastra skills so agents know CLI commands: `npx skills add mastra-ai/skills`.

## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| `user-mastra` **error**, only `mcp_auth` | Upgrade to **Node.js ≥ 22.13.0**, restart Cursor |
| Tools not in chat | Enable in MCP settings; start **new** chat |
| `searchMastraDocs` empty | Fall back to **`mastraDocs`** paths or `mastra.ai/llms.txt` |
| `npx` not found in Cursor | Use absolute path from `which npx` as `"command"` |
| Wrong API in generated code | `grep` `app/node_modules/@mastra/core/dist/docs/references` |
| Dev server / agent run fails | `cd app && infisical run --env=dev -- npm run dev` |

